HEADWORD: Triobolary
<hw>Tri*ob"o*la*ry</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>triobolaris</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>triobolus</ets> a piece of three oboli, Gr. <?/. See
<ets>Tri-</ets>, and <er>Obolus</er>.]</ety> <def>Of the value of three
oboli; hence, mean; worthless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It may pass current . . . for a <qex>triobolar</qex> ballad.</q>
<rj><qau>Cheyne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trioctile</ent>⟦br⟧
